Free camera controls
--------------------
mouse movement      - rotate camera (when in UI mode, push mouse cursor into screen borders)
arrow keys          - rotate camera
Space               - up/increase height
Ctrl                - down/decrease height
Tab                 - toggle interface mode
Numpad Enter        - switch between FreeCam and Strategic camera
i                   - incarnate into the selected bot

Bot controls
------------
mouse movement      - look around (when in UI mode, push mouse cursor into screen borders)
arrow keys          - look around
w, a, s, d          - move forwards, left, backwards, right
Shift               - toggle run
Ctrl                - toggle crouch
Space               - jump

left click          - trigger equipped weapon
right click         - use tagged object or enter tagged vehicle
middle click        - grab/drop tagged object or take an item from the inventory when clicking on an
                      inventory item
wheel up            - throw object you are currently holding
wheel down          - put tagged object into inventory

m                   - suicide
i                   - leave bot
p                   - toggle ability to step over small obstacles, e.g. walk up the stairs

Tab                 - toggle interface mode
Numpad Enter        - switch between 1st persorn and 3rd person camera
Numpad *            - toggle freelook (look around without rotating the bot)

f                   - point gesture
g                   - fall back gesture
h                   - salute gesture
j                   - wave gesture
k                   - flip out gesture
l                   - play all animations

Vehicle controls
----------------
mouse movement      - look around (when in UI mode, push mouse cursor into screen borders)
arrow keys          - look around
w, a, s, d          - move forwards, left, backwards, right
Space               - up (air vehicles) or jump (hover vehicles)
Ctrl                - down (air vehicles)

left click          - trigger selected weapon
wheel up            - select previous weapon
wheel down          - select next weapon

x                   - exit vehicle
j                   - eject from vehicle

Tab                 - toggle interface mode
Numpad Enter        - switch between 1st persorn and 3rd person camera
Numpad *            - toggle freelook (look around without rotating the vehicle)

Misc controls
-------------
o                   - forward sky time for 1/8 of a day

F11                 - screenshot (saved to ~/.openzone/screenshot-DATE.bmp)
F12                 - minimise and freeze (not working on Windows)

Command line
------------
openzone [OPTIONS]

--help
      Prints that help message.

--load, --no-load
-l, -L
      Enables or disables autoload of ~/.openzone/default.ozState on startup respectively.
      Overrides the 'autoload' resource.

--save, --no-save
-s, -S
      Enables or disables autosave to ~/.openzone/default.ozState on exit respectively.
      Overrides the 'autosave' resource.

--time num
-t num
      Exits after num seconds (can be a floating-point number). For benchmarking purposes.

Dependencies
------------
- SDL
- SDL_image (needed for prebuild only, needs at least PNG and JPEG support)
- SDL_ttf
- SDL_net
- OpenGL (MesaGL)
- OpenAL
- FreeALUT
- libvorbis
- Lua

On Linux you have to install packages that provide those libraries.
For Windows build, all dependencies are included.

Notes
-----
- On first run ~/.openzone/client.rc configuration file with default settings is generated.
  Edit it to change any settings you wish.
- On exit the world is saved to ~/.openzone/default.ozState. Delete this file to start with a
  clean world again.
- You can jump to higher places with jump-duck (like in Half-Life 1).
- "~" means $HOME on Linux (i.e. /home/username) and $USERPROFILE on Windows (i.e.
  C:\Documents and Settings\username on Windows XP or C:\Users\username on Windows Vista)
